  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-03 stale dataset)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: The primary experimental dataset carries a dataVintage of 2025-11-03T00:00:00Z, predating the model revision of 2025-11-24T00:00:00Z. The assessment narrative characterises the revision as a minor turbulence-model coefficient adjustment not material to the dataset's hemolysis correlation, but no formal re-validation was conducted against the updated model build.",
